id: hac-gpm3
title: Modernize and secure homeassistant-cli delivery
description: "Eliminate known dependency vulnerabilities, restore reliable automated updates, modernize CI actions, and leave a governed maintenance backlog."
type: Epic
status: in_progress
priority: 0
tags[5]: ci,dependencies,github,governance,security
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:52:35.105Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T17:25:15.449Z"
deadline: "2026-07-18T16:52:35.105Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: "Zero actionable Bun audit advisories after supported upgrades; all local quality, coverage, package, and security gates pass; GitHub dependency and security alerts are cleared or explicitly documented; PM tracker is healthy and contains reproducible evidence; changes are reviewed, merged, and verified on the default branch"
definition_of_ready: "Authenticated GitHub access, clean default-branch baseline, live alert inventory, and repository-local PM tracker available."
goal: secure-reliable-agent-cli
objective: 2026-dependency-and-delivery-hardening
value: Protect Home Assistant operators and keep the agent-facing CLI maintainable.
impact: Removes exploitable dependency paths and makes future automated upgrades verifiable.
outcome: "A current, reproducible, security-gated release pipeline with no stale update backlog."
why_now: "A critical Vitest advisory, multiple high-severity runtime/tooling advisories, and fifteen failing Dependabot PRs are open."
parent: hac-4s9j
reviewer: unbraind
risk: critical
confidence: 95
sprint: 2026-07-security
release: 2026.7.16
resolution: "Removed vulnerable dependency paths, restored reproducible automation, raised quality enforcement, initialized PM governance, reconciled GitHub backlog, and protected master."
expected_result: "A current, reproducible, security-gated repository with no stale update backlog and complete PM evidence."
actual_result: Zero security alerts/open PRs/issues; full merged-head release verification and hosted CI/security pass; master protection and PM tracker health verified.
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  hac-4s9j,parent,"2026-07-16T17:07:03.618Z",codex-root,null
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T16:52:35.105Z",codex-root,"Live baseline: 15 open Dependabot PRs; one critical Dependabot alert GHSA-5xrq-8626-4rwp; zero open CodeQL and secret-scanning alerts."
  "2026-07-16T17:23:47.785Z",codex-root,"Outcome achieved: PR #52 merged as d2c73b2; merged-master release verification and hosted CI/Security passed; dependency, code-scanning, secret-scanning, issue, and PR backlogs are empty; master is protected; all seven remediation children are closed with reproducible evidence."
  "2026-07-16T17:25:15.427Z",codex-root,Reopened after Dependabot generated new grouped PRs #53 and #54 immediately following the completed bootstrap. The same remediation lineage remains canonical until valid new Action majors are adopted and incompatible toolchain churn is constrained.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T16:52:35.105Z",codex-root,Representative PR checks fail at bun install --frozen-lockfile because package.json and bun.lock diverge.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T16:52:35.105Z",codex-root,Dependency PRs must update bun.lock coherently; otherwise every CI job fails before exercising the proposed update.
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  package.json,project,Dependency policy and scripts
tests[1]{command,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  "bun run test:coverage",project,1800
docs[2]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/RELEASING.md,project,Release verification contract
  SECURITY.md,project,Security policy and reporting baseline
body: "## Scope\\n\\nSecurity remediation, dependency modernization, CI reproducibility, GitHub Actions maintenance, repository inspection, governed delivery, and merged-head proof.\\n\\n## Live baseline\\n\\n- 15 open Dependabot PRs\\n- Critical Vitest alert GHSA-5xrq-8626-4rwp / CVE-2026-47429\\n- 28 local Bun audit findings across runtime and development dependency paths\\n- Representative PRs fail frozen install because bun.lock is stale\\n- No open CodeQL or secret-scanning alerts"
